Network Security: hardware and software solutions to achieve the set security goals

Examples of hardware appliances:
-firewall appliance
-intrusion detection system
-intrusion prevention system
-virtual private network

Examples of software
-Antivirus software
-Host firewall: eg. Windows Defender Firewall

Cyber Kill Chain
1. Recon: gather information
2. Weaponization: prep file with malicious component
3. Delivery: deliver malicious component eg. email or flash memory
4. Exploit: once malicious compnent executes and installs malicious component on target system
5. command and control: control of target system
6. Post Exploit: objetives such as data exfiltration executed 

------------------

nmap 10.10.10.10

result: 
21/tcp FTP
22/tcp ssh
80/tcp http

FTP: file transfer protocol
SSH: secure shell
HTTP: hypertext transfer protocol

